1
00:00:00,045 --> 00:00:05,605
Welcome to Skillberry Store — a smart skills repository
for agentic workflows.

2
00:00:09,021 --> 00:00:16,186
Skillberry Store centralises every tool your AI agents
need. Upload once, execute anywhere. It manages tools,

3
00:00:16,236 --> 00:00:23,401
skills, and snippets with semantic search, lifecycle
management, virtual MCP servers, and a plugin ecosystem.

4
00:00:24,017 --> 00:00:30,235
Installation is simple. Install with pip, optionally
bundle the AI plugins. Run with Docker using a single make

5
00:00:30,285 --> 00:00:36,503
command. The web UI starts on port 8002, the REST API on
8000, and the MCP control endpoint is ready for any AI

6
00:00:36,553 --> 00:00:42,772
client.

7
00:00:44,035 --> 00:00:52,585
The auto-generated CLI is called sbs. Built on restish, it
mirrors every REST endpoint. Run sbs connect to point it

8
00:00:52,635 --> 00:01:01,185
at your server. Skills, tools, snippets, virtual servers,
and admin commands are all available.

9
00:01:02,004 --> 00:01:09,428
Let's import a skill. Three paths are supported: GitHub
URL, zip file, or local folder. Here we point the API at

10
00:01:09,478 --> 00:01:16,902
the PPTX skill on disk. The response confirms 66 tools and
43 snippets created in one call.

11
00:01:18,019 --> 00:01:22,693
The web UI starts automatically. From the dashboard
navigate to Skills, Tools, Snippets, virtual servers,

12
00:01:22,743 --> 00:01:27,416
Plugins, Observability, and Admin.

13
00:01:28,021 --> 00:01:34,465
The Skills library shows our two imported skills — pptx
with 66 tools, summarizer with 29. Tags like

14
00:01:34,515 --> 00:01:40,959
quality-score, performance-score, and security-score were
auto-applied by the AI plugins on import.

15
00:01:42,038 --> 00:01:50,681
The Import Anthropic Skill dialog offers three sources:
GitHub URL, zip file for air-gapped environments, or local

16
00:01:50,731 --> 00:01:59,373
folder for CI/CD pipelines. One click imports the full
skill tree — tools, snippets, and documentation.

17
00:02:00,042 --> 00:02:06,464
Here's the pptx skill after import — 66 tools, 43
snippets, full metadata. You can export back to Anthropic

18
00:02:06,514 --> 00:02:12,937
format, edit metadata, or delete with a cascade option to
clean up all linked objects.

19
00:02:14,022 --> 00:02:20,598
The Summarizer skill: 29 tools, 2 snippets. The evaluator
scored it 9 out of 10 for quality, 8 for performance, 8

20
00:02:20,648 --> 00:02:27,224
for security. Scores are searchable and filterable across
the library.

21
00:02:28,050 --> 00:02:34,825
The Tools page shows all 95 tools in one sortable table.
Filter by tags, switch between text and semantic search,

22
00:02:34,875 --> 00:02:41,649
and select multiple tools for bulk export or deletion.

23
00:02:44,034 --> 00:02:50,098
Clicking a tool opens its detail page — programming
language, packaging format, dependencies, and the JSON

24
00:02:50,148 --> 00:02:56,213
parameter schema. A Source Code tab shows the raw Python
module.

25
00:02:57,049 --> 00:03:04,681
Hit Execute to run a tool. Parameters go in as JSON, and
the tool runs inside a Docker sandbox — isolated from the

26
00:03:04,731 --> 00:03:12,364
host. From the CLI: sbs execute-tool with a body flag.
Same sandbox, scriptable.

27
00:03:13,050 --> 00:03:17,383
Snippets are code fragments and docs imported with the
skill. Syntax-highlighted and searchable — perfect for

28
00:03:17,433 --> 00:03:21,766
shared utility code.

29
00:03:23,001 --> 00:03:28,128
Virtual MCP Servers expose a skill's tools as a standalone
MCP endpoint. Each gets its own port and SSE URL — connect

30
00:03:28,178 --> 00:03:33,305
Claude, Cursor, or any MCP client directly.

31
00:03:34,003 --> 00:03:38,481
Virtual NFS Servers expose a skill as a mountable
read-only filesystem over WebDAV or NFSv3 — Claude Code

32
00:03:38,531 --> 00:03:43,009
and rclone can read files without the REST API.

33
00:03:44,049 --> 00:03:48,686
The Plugins page shows all AI-powered extensions. Enable
or disable each independently. Let's walk through the five

34
00:03:48,736 --> 00:03:53,373
key plugins.

35
00:03:58,022 --> 00:04:03,070
The Content Evaluator tags skills and tools with quality,
performance, and security scores. The Summarizer scored 9

36
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:08,168
for quality, 8 for performance, 8 for security. Each score
includes a written explanation. Triggered on import or on

37
00:04:08,218 --> 00:04:13,266
demand.

38
00:04:14,026 --> 00:04:19,069
The Security Evaluator finds vulnerabilities — path
traversal, injection, missing auth. The pptx skill scored

39
00:04:19,119 --> 00:04:24,162
4 out of 10 because it accepts arbitrary file paths with
no validation. Visible as a security-score tag before you

40
00:04:24,212 --> 00:04:29,256
deploy.

41
00:04:30,027 --> 00:04:37,406
The Skill Deduplicator uses LLM semantic comparison to
find near-identical skills. When duplicates are found, a

42
00:04:37,456 --> 00:04:44,834
notification appears with Keep or Delete decisions. The
decision API lets you automate this in CI pipelines.

43
00:04:46,023 --> 00:04:53,605
The Snippet Creator generates code from a natural language
description. Describe what you want, the LLM writes it,

44
00:04:53,655 --> 00:05:01,238
infers the language and tags, and saves it to the store.
No copy-paste. Works with OpenAI, WatsonX, or LiteLLM.

45
00:05:02,038 --> 00:05:09,584
The Skill Optimizer exports a skill, runs Claude Code in a
RunSpace container, and imports the optimized result with

46
00:05:09,634 --> 00:05:17,180
an optimized suffix. Rationale and changes are saved as
metadata. Safe to re-run any time.

47
00:05:18,072 --> 00:05:25,690
From the CLI, use sbs search-tools to find the right tool,
then sbs execute-tool with a JSON body. Results pipe into

48
00:05:25,740 --> 00:05:33,357
jq, files, or any CI pipeline. Every operation is
scriptable.

49
00:05:34,026 --> 00:05:40,616
Built-in observability: live time-series charts for
skills, tools, snippets, and system metrics. Prometheus on

50
00:05:40,666 --> 00:05:47,257
port 8090. Jaeger traces. Drop a Grafana dashboard on top
for full monitoring.

51
00:05:48,028 --> 00:05:55,599
The architecture is layered: Web UI and REST API at the
top, MCP frontend and virtual NFS alongside, core data

52
00:05:55,649 --> 00:06:03,220
model in the middle, Docker sandbox and pluggable storage
below, and the AI plugin layer at the base.

53
00:06:04,039 --> 00:06:11,383
That's Skillberry Store — one service for every skill your
agents need. Install with pip, start with make docker-run,

54
00:06:11,433 --> 00:06:18,777
live in under a minute. Find us at github.com slash
skillberry-ai slash skillberry-store.

